    <list type="translations">
        <item xml:lang="zh">煙囪</item>
    </list>
<div type="definition">
<p>TUBE OR HOLE IN a ROOF THROUGH which SMOKE LEAVES a STOVE.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. There is only one term for a chimney, tū 突, and archeological evidence suggests that the chimney took the form of a hole in the roof.</p>
<p>NB: Words like cōng 囪 and yān cōng 煙囪 are all late.</p>
        </div>
<div type="modern-chinese-criteria">
<p>煙囪 yāncong is the current modern word for a chimney.</p>
<p>煙筒</p>
<p>煙突</p>
